This statement, made by the President on the 38th anniversary of the Roe v. Wade Supreme Court decision, expresses support for the protection of women's health and reproductive freedom. The President emphasizes the importance of not allowing the government to interfere in private family matters. He states his commitment to upholding this constitutional right and highlights the need for policies, initiatives, and programs that prevent unintended pregnancies, support pregnant women and mothers, promote healthy relationships, and encourage adoption. The President also calls for a broader commitment to ensuring that daughters have the same rights, freedoms, and opportunities as sons to pursue their dreams.